com.i2group.apollo.model.data.transport

Class Item

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.i2group.apollo.model.data.transport.CoreItem
      • com.i2group.apollo.model.data.transport.Item
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    Entity, Link

    public abstract class Item
extends CoreItem
    A generic representation for Entitys and Links that provides the features common to both. In particular, Items give access to the Cards that store Property data, to the collection of PrimaryPropertyIdentifiers, and to the ItemType identifier.

    Items are also the basis of the i2 Analyze versioning model, which records every change made to every Item in the Analysis Repository. This provides the ability to examine the history of changes to data, allowing the user to see the state of Items at any point in time.

    There are restrictions on the operations that clients can perform, depending on the version of an Item they attempt to operate upon. The documentation for the command service, the item retrieval service, and the search service explain these features in detail. Broadly:

    • Searching in i2 Analyze only considers the latest versions of items.
    • Clients can only take leases on the latest versions of items.
    • As a result of the above, clients can only modify the most recent versions of items.
    • Sets retain items at the versions they had when they were added to the set, unless a client explicitly updates them.
    • Clients can create links between entities in a set when they are not the latest versions. This is not the case for entities outside sets.
    These restrictions are further reinforced by the strongly typed item identifiers that i2 Analyze uses. Operations that need to check versions require item identifiers that include version details.
    Since:
    1.0

      • isSupplanted

        public final boolean isSupplanted()
        Indicates whether this Item was supplanted as a result of acting as the source in a merge operation.
        Returns:
        true if this Item was supplanted; false otherwise.

        If this Item was supplanted and getMergeTargetItemIdentifier() returns null, then this Item is a reflexive Link.

        Since:
        4.0

      • getPrimaryPropertyIdentifiers

        public final Collection<PrimaryPropertyIdentifier> getPrimaryPropertyIdentifiers()
        Gets the PrimaryPropertyIdentifiers of the primary properties that have been set for this Item.

        A PrimaryPropertyIdentifier identifies the specific Property of a particular type that contains the value for clients to use in labels, search results, and filter operations. At most, the collection contains one PrimaryPropertyIdentifier for each PropertyType that this Item can contain.

        Returns:
        See above.
        Since:
        4.0
